FuncDef: The display elabel power-backplane command displays information about the E-labels on the power backplane.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
An E-label contains information about the board type, bar code, bill of material (BOM) code, English description, date of manufacture, vendor name, issuing number, common language equipment identification (CLEI) code, and sales BOM code.
You can use the display elabel power-backplane command to view information about E-labels on the power backplane, which helps monitor the device status.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
